data.description: Welcome to 1524 E. Wilt St., where creativity meets character in this unique carriage house, thoughtfully redesigned to inspire and delight. If you're seeking a non-traditional property with a distinctive flair, look no further – this is the place for you.  Step through the striking custom wood 'garage door' entryway, accessible through the adjacent traditional yellow door or opened from within to seamlessly connect with the outdoors. Previously a storage area, this space has been transformed into a versatile 'all-season' room, featuring overhead heat lamps, lighting, a new plumbing setup for a wine fridge, a custom-built sofa/couch, imported Spanish tiles, and updated electricals. Whether it's a cozy retreat for winter gatherings or a breezy outdoor extension for summer entertaining, this space offers endless possibilities.  Ascend the staircase to the upstairs living area, where a spacious living room, a stylish half bath, and a concealed laundry closet await. The open floor plan leads to the kitchen with a central island and a separate dining area. Tucked into the living room wall is a thoughtfully designed pet room, complete with wallpaper, soft bedding, and a grated doorway – a haven for furry companions.  A spiral staircase leads to the third level, revealing yet another expansive living area that can be tailored to your needs – whether it's a den, office, or bonus room. Currently set up as a den/tv room, this level also features a smaller bedroom and a large primary bedroom with cathedral-style slanted ceilings. A brand new bathroom with a sophisticated black and white palette and stunning green Spanish tile flooring adds a touch of modern elegance. This level also offers a separate exit/entry through a side hallway leading to the street-level foyer.  The layout is truly unique and has been tastefully restructured to accommodate a variety of living options. Additionally, a custom plug has been conveniently installed next to the 'garage' doors for electric vehicle charging. The sidewalk in front of the entry has been utilized for parking by the current and past owners. Nestled on the quiet neighborhood street of Wilt St., this home is surrounded by neighborly and cooperative residents.  Fishtown has emerged as a sought-after neighborhood, known for its walkability and an array of top-rated restaurants in the city. This vibrant area offers a thriving community and a location that truly embodies the spirit of creativity and urban living.
